/>
created another variable to store the postal code regular expression which we will be discussing in a second.<br
/>
Then I used the test function to test my string against the regular expression and print the result in an alert.</p><p>Now let’s jump to the regular expression itself:</p><p>UK postal code examples :<br
/>
EC1A 1BB<br
/>
W1A 0AX<br
/>
M1 1AE<br
/>
B33 8TH<br
/>
CR2 6XH<br
/>
DN55 1PT<br
/>
So, 1 or 2 alphabetic characters, followed by  1 or 2 digits, then a space and one digit and exactly two alphabetic characters.<br
/>
So here is the Regular expression pattern:</p><p>/^[A-Z]{1,2}[0-9]{1,2} ?[0-9][A-Z]{2}$/i</p><p>The i at the end of the pattern is to indicate that this is a case insensitive match.</p><p>Here is the demo code:</p><p
