/>
This simple regular expression just checks for 2 digits / 2 digits / 4 digits date format</p><p>If you want more complex, tight validation for mm/dd/yyyy format, here is the format<br
/>
<code>/^(0[1-9]|1[0-2])\/(0[1-9]|1\d|2\d|3[01])\/(19|20)\d{2}$/</code></p><p><a
href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/15196623">source</a></p><li>URL</li><p>A URL of the format http(s)://website/page can be validated with this regular expression:<br
/>
<code><br
/>
https?:\/\/(www\.)?[-a-zA-Z0-9@:%._\+~#=]{2,256}\.[a-z]{2,6}\b([-a-zA-Z0-9@:%_\+.~#?&amp;//=]*)<br
/>
</code></p><p><a
href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/3809435">source</a></p><li>Any Alpha Numeric String</li><p>If you want to allow only alphanumeric characters, use this regular expression:<br
/>
<code>/^[a-zA-Z0-9]*$/</code></p><li>Decimal Numbers</li><p>For decimal numbers with one decimal point, the regular expression is:<br
/>
<code>/^[0-9]+\.?[0-9]*$/</code></p></ol></div>
</article>
